HEADWORD: Sterility
<hw>Ste*ril"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sterilitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>st⟦eacute⟧rilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or condition of being sterile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Quality of being sterile;
infecundity; also, the state of being free from germs or
spores.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sterilization</ent>⟦br⟧
